data.content:
Danh từ
sự phạm pháp
juvenile delinquency
sự phạm pháp của thanh thiếu niên
sự chểnh mảng, sự lơ là (nhiệm vụ)

noun
plural -cies
crimes or other morally wrong acts :illegal or immoral behavior especially by young people [noncount]
They tried to steer him away from delinquency by giving him a job in their store.
She's been charged with contributing to the delinquency of a minor. [count]
a series of minor delinquencies - see also juvenile delinquency
US :the condition of someone who owes money and is not making payments at the required or expected time [count]
Loan delinquencies are on the rise. [=an increasing number of people are failing to make their loan payments on time] [noncount]
a high rate of delinquency
Delinquency rates are soaring.
